## Conferences

- Beccard, M. (07.04.25). <a href="https://lingcomm.org/2025/03/10/lightning-talks-lingcomm25/">"How to pass the bar as a linguist"</a>. LingComm25 online.

- Albrecht, S., Isiaka, A., Ivanova, M. (15.07.23). <a href="https://tuc.cloud/index.php/s/2dJMWmZCooa29gr" target="_blank">"Igbo and Yoruba English vowel spaces compared"</a>. Digital English World Wide in Chemnitz.

- Albrecht, S., Schmied, J., Ivanova, M. (15-17.06.23). "Comparing vowel spaces across three circles: A quantitative corpus-based approach" IAWE25.

- Schmied, J., Albrecht, S., Ivanova, M. (15-17.06.23). "Empirical perception studies on Italian English: Neglected, charming or unaccepted?". IAWE25.

- Ivanova, M. (17-25.05.23). "Competent but cold: Learning outcomes using a pedagogical agent speaking native and non-native varieties". Alexander-von-Humboldt Linguistic Marathon "Empirical English Studies: Discourse-, Corpus-, Psycho- & Computer-Linguistic Approaches" in Brno (CZ), Klagenfurt (AT), Padova, Ferrara, and Modena (IT).

- Albrecht & Ivanova, M. (30.08.22). <a href="https://tuc.cloud/index.php/s/AsrfXfmrxRiCHWK" target="_blank">"Talking about news articles related to the Covid Pandemic on Twitter. Global Discourse and Intertextuality"</a>. Talk at the European Society for the Study of English Conference 2022 Mainz. GitLab repository: <a href="https://mytuc.org/vkjk" target="_blank">https://mytuc.org/vkjk</a>

- Ivanova, M. (07.06.22). <a href="https://tuc.cloud/index.php/s/pxQeBZi3FStH8Ts" target="_blank">"German English-medium linguistics journal abstracts over the last 30 years: Quantitative and qualitative structural developments."</a> Talk at the Summer School Digital Humanities at the University of Modena and Reggio Emilia (Italy) 06-10 June 2022.

- Ivanova, M. (26.05.22). <a href="https://tuc.cloud/index.php/s/6RqXp8xbTty3gPP" target="_blank">"Open digital peer conference reviews: Towards a transparent constructive critical discourse to advance science"</a>. Talk at the online International Conference “Digital Genres and Open Science” at the University of Zaragoza (Spain) 26-27 May 2022.

- Schmied, J. & Ivanova, M. (02.09.21). <a href="https://tuc.cloud/index.php/s/gXmiikLmTz8Jn7t" target="_blank">"Academic Writing Conventions in English MA Theses before and after Bologna: Global Rhetorical Structures and Stance in Sub-Disciplines at a German University"</a>. Seminar talk at the 2021 online ESSE conference.

- Ivanova, M. & Schmied, J. (10.08.20). <a href="https://tuc.cloud/index.php/s/m52AtZEsi3p4jcW" target="_blank">"Uncertainty in postgraduate training and supervision: A needs analysis for online course development"</a>. Digital English World-Wide conference online.

- Ivanova, M. (06.07.19). “Semantic and pragmatic truth implications of concession in single- and double-blind open peer review.” Digital English World-Wide conference in Chemnitz.

